{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id5a447583-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c","identifier":"/us/usc/t29/s257"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"257"},"text":"§ 257.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Pending collective and representative actions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The statute of limitations prescribed in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s255/b"},"text":"section 255(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall also be applicable (in the case of a collective or representative action commenced prior to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 1947","children":[],"tail":" under the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938, as amended ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s201"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 201","children":[],"tail":" et seq.]) to an individual claimant who has not been specifically named as a party plaintiff to the action prior to the expiration of one hundred and twenty days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1947-05-14"},"text":"May 14, 1947","children":[],"tail":". In the application of such statute of limitations such action shall be considered to have been commenced as to him when, and only when, his written consent to become a party plaintiff to the action is filed in the court in which the action was brought."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id5a447584-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-05-14/ch52/s8"},"text":"May 14, 1947, ch. 52, § 8","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/88"},"text":"61 Stat. 88","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id5a447585-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id5a447586-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id5a447587-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938, as amended, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1938-06-25/ch676"},"text":"act June 25, 1938, ch. 676","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/52/1060"},"text":"52 Stat. 1060","children":[],"tail":", as amended, which is classified generally to chapter 8 (§ 201 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s201"},"text":"section 201 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
